“Whatever you do, do it with passion”

I can’t believe it’s going to be 10 years since i started @befit_nutrition from my mothers 2 bedroom townhouse. The trials and tribulations alongside with the hardships of starting a business with zero capital, zero investors and zero knowledge has been one of the toughest journeys i have ever embarked on in my life but at the end of the day i wouldn’t change it for anything in the world because it has made me wiser, stronger and more resilient to everything in life and built me into the fearless bold business man that i am today.

If you have a dream, if you have a goal, if you have something you are truly passionate about then go get it! fight for it! Sacrifice yourself for it and strive to be the best at it. Bring true value to others, care for your clients like they are your own family and always have the mentality of bringing the absolute best service and quality to your clients, if you do all these things and you don’t give up when adversity arrives i guarantee you will be successful 💯
Grateful for the family God has blessed me with 🙏🏻 #Blessed
Think back on all the hard times you've gotten through already…This one will soon be a memory as well #KeepGoing #TodoConDios

“Whoever is kind to the poor lends to the LORD, and he will reward them for what they have done.” -Proverbs 19:17

I never forget getting on my knees praying to God in the living room of the house i was renting to operate my business illegally since we did not have enough money to rent a fully certified commercial kitchen to operate our business. I recall speaking to God telling him that if this business was meant to be for me that he would make a way and that i wanted him to use me in his name to help others and to give back to the less fortunate. I asked him to guide me in the path to be successful and i promised to him i would  use my resources and my success to help and lift others up in anyway or form possible, until this day i still pray to to him to use my business in his glory to serve and help others. Even though i am no where near successful and my business is still nowhere i would like it to be; we are much better than we were before and my promise to God remains faithful; to help others and lift others as he has lifted me and my business.

I love you father #godisgood
God is Good 🙏🏻 #Blessed

You-vs-You

One of the greatest and most fulfilling feelings you can feel within your heart is the accomplishment of helping others, no material or physical thing in this world can give you the soul fulfillment within your heart that helping others does. 

Ever since i started @befit_nutrition from my mothers townhouse in 2014 i have always prayed to God for him to give me the resources to help others and for him you use me in his will to help others,  i always promised him that every blessing that he laid upon me i would pass on to help others. 

I am truly blessed to be able to give the testimony that God listens to all of our prayers and that i now take great pride to constantly help the homeless and the less fortunate, i don’t do this for no benefit, no tax cut, i don’t even claim these donations to my accountant or to any company for a benefit but i do it to bring awareness to encourage others to do the same; not in the exact way of passing out food but in anyway or form that you can to help others, the homeless, the ill, the sick, the poor, the less fortunate, just anybody in need of help and I promise if you open up your heart you will experience a soul fulfilling feeling in your heart that cannot be compared to anything. Bless others with what God has blessed you with and the doors or heavens will open up for you.

Proverbs 19:17: “Whoever is kind to the poor lends to the LORD, and he will reward them for what they have done.”
